00056   class Spec {
00057   protected:
00059     const int* data;
00061     int l, u;
00062   public:
00064     bool valid(void) const {
00065       return data != NULL;
00066     }
00068     int capacity(void) const {
00069       return data[0];
00070     }
00072     int items(void) const {
00073       return data[1];
00074     }
00076     int size(int i) const {
00077       return data[i+2];
00078     }
00079   protected:
00081     static const int* find(const char* s) {
00082       for (int i=0; name[i] != NULL; i++)
00083         if (!strcmp(s,name[i]))
00084           return bpp[i];
00085       return NULL;
00086     }
00088     int clower(void) const {
00089       /*
00090        * The lower bound is due to: S. Martello, P. Toth. Lower bounds
00091        * and reduction procedures for the bin packing problem.
00092        * Discrete and applied mathematics, 28(1):59-70, 1990.
00093        */
00094       const int c = capacity(), n = items();
00095       int l = 0;
00096 
00097       // Items in N1 are from 0 ... n1 - 1
00098       int n1 = 0;
00099       // Items in N2 are from n1 ... n12 - 1, we count elements in N1 and N2
00100       int n12 = 0;
00101       // Items in N3 are from n12 ... n3 - 1
00102       int n3 = 0;
00103       // Free space in N2
00104       int f2 = 0;
00105       // Total size of items in N3
00106       int s3 = 0;
00107 
00108       // Initialize n12 and f2
00109       for (; (n12 < n) && (size(n12) > c/2); n12++)
00110         f2 += c - size(n12);
00111 
00112       // Initialize n3 and s3
00113       for (n3 = n12; n3 < n; n3++)
00114         s3 += size(n3);
00115 
00116       // Compute lower bounds
00117       for (int k=0; k<=c/2; k++) {
00118         // Make N1 larger by adding elements and N2 smaller
00119         for (; (n1 < n) && (size(n1) > c-k); n1++)
00120           f2 -= c - size(n1);
00121         assert(n1 <= n12);
00122         // Make N3 smaller by removing elements
00123         for (; (size(n3-1) < k) && (n3 > n12); n3--)
00124           s3 -= size(n3-1);
00125         // Overspill
00126         int o = (s3 > f2) ? ((s3 - f2 + c - 1) / c) : 0;
00127         l = std::max(l, n12 + o);
00128       }
00129       return l;
00130     }
00132     int cupper(void) const {
00133       // Use a naive greedy algorithm
00134       const int c = capacity(), n = items();
00135 
00136       int* f = new int[n];
00137       for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00138         f[i] = c;
00139 
00140       int u=0;
00141       for (int i=0; i<n; i++) {
00142         int j=0;
00143         // Skip bins with insufficient free space
00144         while (f[j] < size(i))
00145           j++;
00146         if (j > u) {
00147           // A new bin is needed
00148           u = j; f[u] -= size(i);
00149         } else {
00150           // The slack of the best-fit bin
00151           int b = j++;
00152           int s = f[b] - size(i);
00153           while (j <= u) {
00154             if ((f[j] >= size(i)) && (f[j] - size(i) < s)) {
00155               b = j; s = f[b] - size(i);
00156             }
00157             j++;
00158           }
00159           f[b] -= size(i);
00160         }
00161       }
00162       delete [] f;
00163       return u+1;
00164     }
00165   public:
00167     Spec(const char* s) : data(find(s)), l(0), u(0) {
00168       if (valid()) {
00169         l = clower(); u = cupper();
00170       }
00171     }
00173     int total(void) const {
00174       int t=0;
00175       for (int i=0; i<items(); i++)
00176         t += size(i);
00177       return t;
00178     }
00180     int lower(void) const {
00181       return l;
00182     }
00184     int upper(void) const {
00185       return u;
00186     }
00187   };
00188 
00189 }

00202 class CDBF : public Brancher {
00203 protected:
00205   ViewArray<Int::IntView> load;
00207   ViewArray<Int::IntView> bin;
00209   IntSharedArray size;
00211   mutable int item;
00213   class Choice : public Gecode::Choice {
00214   public:
00216     int item;
00218     int* same;
00220     int n_same;
00224     Choice(const Brancher& b, unsigned int a, int i, int* s, int n_s)
00225       : Gecode::Choice(b,a), item(i),
00226         same(heap.alloc<int>(n_s)), n_same(n_s) {
00227       for (int k=n_same; k--; )
00228         same[k] = s[k];
00229     }
00231     virtual void archive(Archive& e) const {
00232       Gecode::Choice::archive(e);
00233       e << alternatives() << item << n_same;
00234       for (int i=n_same; i--;)
00235         e << same[i];
00236     }
00238     virtual ~Choice(void) {
00239       heap.free<int>(same,n_same);
00240     }
00241   };
00242 
00243 public:
00245   CDBF(Home home, ViewArray<Int::IntView>& l, ViewArray<Int::IntView>& b,
00246        IntSharedArray& s)
00247     : Brancher(home), load(l), bin(b), size(s), item(0) {
00248     home.notice(*this,AP_DISPOSE);
00249   }
00251   static void post(Home home, ViewArray<Int::IntView>& l,
00252                    ViewArray<Int::IntView>& b,
00253                    IntSharedArray& s) {
00254     (void) new (home) CDBF(home, l, b, s);
00255   }
00257   CDBF(Space& home, CDBF& cdbf)
00258     : Brancher(home, cdbf), size(cdbf.size), item(cdbf.item) {
00259     load.update(home, cdbf.load);
00260     bin.update(home, cdbf.bin);
00261   }
00263   virtual Actor* copy(Space& home) {
00264     return new (home) CDBF(home, *this);
00265   }
00267   virtual size_t dispose(Space& home) {
00268     home.ignore(*this,AP_DISPOSE);
00269     size.~IntSharedArray();
00270     (void) Brancher::dispose(home);
00271     return sizeof(*this);
00272   }
00274   virtual bool status(const Space&) const {
00275     for (int i = item; i < bin.size(); i++)
00276       if (!bin[i].assigned()) {
00277         item = i; return true;
00278       }
00279     return false;
00280   }
00282   virtual Gecode::Choice* choice(Space&) {
00283     assert(!bin[item].assigned());
00284 
00285     int n = bin.size(), m = load.size();
00286 
00287     Region region;
00288 
00289     // Free space in bins
00290     int* free = region.alloc<int>(m);
00291 
00292     for (int j=m; j--; )
00293       free[j] = load[j].max();
00294     for (int i=n; i--; )
00295       if (bin[i].assigned())
00296         free[bin[i].val()] -= size[i];
00297 
00298     // Equivalent bins with same free space
00299     int* same = region.alloc<int>(m+1);
00300     unsigned int n_same = 0;
00301     unsigned int n_possible = 0;
00302 
00303     // Initialize such that failure is guaranteed (pack into bin -1)
00304     same[n_same++] = -1;
00305 
00306     // Find a best-fit bin for item
00307     int slack = INT_MAX;
00308     for (Int::ViewValues<Int::IntView> j(bin[item]); j(); ++j)
00309       if (size[item] <= free[j.val()]) {
00310         // Item still can fit into the bin
00311         n_possible++;
00312         if (free[j.val()] - size[item] < slack) {
00313           // A new, better fit
00314           slack = free[j.val()] - size[item];
00315           same[0] = j.val(); n_same = 1;
00316         } else if (free[j.val()] - size[item] == slack) {
00317           // An equivalent bin, remember it
00318           same[n_same++] = j.val();
00319         }
00320       }
00321     /*
00322      * Domination rules:
00323      *  - if the item fits the bin exactly, just assign
00324      *  - if all possible bins are equivalent, just assign
00325      *
00326      * Also catches failure: if no possible bin was found, commit
00327      * the item into bin -1.
00328      */
00329     if ((slack == 0) || (n_same == n_possible) || (slack == INT_MAX))
00330       return new Choice(*this, 1, item, same, 1);
00331     else
00332       return new Choice(*this, 2, item, same, n_same);
00333   }
00335   virtual const Gecode::Choice* choice(const Space&, Archive& e) {
00336     int alt, item, n_same;
00337     e >> alt >> item >> n_same;
00338     Region re;
00339     int* same = re.alloc<int>(n_same);
00340     for (int i=n_same; i--;) e >> same[i];
00341     return new Choice(*this, alt, item, same, n_same);
00342   }
00344   virtual ExecStatus commit(Space& home, const Gecode::Choice& _c,
00345                             unsigned int a) {
00346     const Choice& c = static_cast<const Choice&>(_c);
00347     // This catches also the case that the choice has a single aternative only
00348     if (a == 0) {
00349       GECODE_ME_CHECK(bin[c.item].eq(home, c.same[0]));
00350     } else {
00351       Iter::Values::Array same(c.same, c.n_same);
00352 
00353       GECODE_ME_CHECK(bin[c.item].minus_v(home, same));
00354 
00355       for (int i = c.item+1; (i<bin.size()) &&
00356                              (size[i] == size[c.item]); i++) {
00357         same.reset();
00358         GECODE_ME_CHECK(bin[i].minus_v(home, same));
00359       }
00360     }
00361     return ES_OK;
00362   }
00364   virtual void print(const Space&, const Gecode::Choice& _c,
00365                      unsigned int a,
00366                      std::ostream& o) const {
00367     const Choice& c = static_cast<const Choice&>(_c);
00368     if (a == 0) {
00369       o << "bin[" << c.item << "] = " << c.same[0];
00370     } else {
00371       o << "bin[" << c.item;
00372       for (int i = c.item+1; (i<bin.size()) &&
00373                              (size[i] == size[c.item]); i++)
00374         o << "," << i;
00375       o << "] != ";
00376       for (int i = 0; i<c.n_same-1; i++)
00377         o << c.same[i] << ",";
00378       o << c.same[c.n_same-1];
00379     }
00380   }
00381 };
00382 
00384 void cdbf(Home home, const IntVarArgs& l, const IntVarArgs& b,
00385           const IntArgs& s) {
00386   if (b.size() != s.size())
00387     throw Int::ArgumentSizeMismatch("cdbf");
00388   ViewArray<Int::IntView> load(home, l);
00389   ViewArray<Int::IntView> bin(home, b);
00390   IntSharedArray size(s);
00391   return CDBF::post(home, load, bin, size);
00392 }

00402 class BinPacking : public IntMinimizeScript {
00403 protected:
00405   const Spec spec;
00407   IntVarArray load;
00409   IntVarArray bin;
00411   IntVar bins;
00412 public:
00414   enum {
00415     MODEL_NAIVE, 
00416     MODEL_PACKING 
00417   };
00419   enum {
00420     BRANCH_NAIVE, 
00421     BRANCH_CDBF, 
00422   };
00424   BinPacking(const InstanceOptions& opt)
00425     : IntMinimizeScript(opt),
00426       spec(opt.instance()),
00427       load(*this, spec.upper(), 0, spec.capacity()),
00428       bin(*this, spec.items(), 0, spec.upper()-1),
00429       bins(*this, spec.lower(), spec.upper()) {
00430     // Number of items
00431     int n = bin.size();
00432     // Number of bins
00433     int m = load.size();
00434 
00435     // Size of all items
00436     int s = 0;
00437     for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00438       s += spec.size(i);
00439 
00440     // Array of sizes
00441     IntArgs sizes(n);
00442     for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00443       sizes[i] = spec.size(i);
00444 
00445     switch (opt.model()) {
00446     case MODEL_NAIVE:
00447       {
00448         // All loads must add up to all item sizes
00449         linear(*this, load, IRT_EQ, s);
00450 
00451         // Load must be equal to packed items
00452         BoolVarArgs _x(*this, n*m, 0, 1);
00453         Matrix<BoolVarArgs> x(_x, n, m);
00454 
00455         for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00456           channel(*this, x.col(i), bin[i]);
00457 
00458         for (int j=0; j<m; j++)
00459           linear(*this, sizes, x.row(j), IRT_EQ, load[j]);
00460       }
00461       break;
00462     case MODEL_PACKING:
00463       binpacking(*this, load, bin, sizes);
00464       break;
00465     }
00466 
00467     // Break symmetries
00468     for (int i=1; i<n; i++)
00469       if (spec.size(i-1) == spec.size(i))
00470         rel(*this, bin[i-1] <= bin[i]);
00471 
00472     // Pack items that require a bin for sure! (wlog)
00473     {
00474       int i = 0;
00475       // These items all need a bin due to their own size
00476       for (; (i < n) && (i < m) && (spec.size(i) * 2 > spec.capacity()); i++)
00477         rel(*this, bin[i] == i);
00478       // Check if the next item cannot fit to position i-1
00479       if ((i < n) && (i < m) && (i > 0) &&
00480           (spec.size(i-1) + spec.size(i) > spec.capacity()))
00481         rel(*this, bin[i] == i);
00482     }
00483 
00484     // All excess bins must be empty
00485     for (int j=spec.lower()+1; j <= spec.upper(); j++)
00486       rel(*this, (bins < j) == (load[j-1] == 0));
00487 
00488     branch(*this, bins, INT_VAL_MIN());
00489     switch (opt.branching()) {
00490     case BRANCH_NAIVE:
00491       branch(*this, bin, INT_VAR_NONE(), INT_VAL_MIN());
00492       break;
00493     case BRANCH_CDBF:
00494       cdbf(*this, load, bin, sizes);
00495       break;
00496     }
00497   }
00499   virtual IntVar cost(void) const {
00500     return bins;
00501   }
00503   BinPacking(BinPacking& s)
00504     : IntMinimizeScript(s), spec(s.spec) {
00505     load.update(*this, s.load);
00506     bin.update(*this, s.bin);
00507     bins.update(*this, s.bins);
00508   }
00510   virtual Space*
00511   copy(void) {
00512     return new BinPacking(*this);
00513   }
00515   virtual void
00516   print(std::ostream& os) const {
00517     int n = bin.size();
00518     int m = load.size();
00519     os << "Bins used: " << bins << " (from " << m << " bins)." << std::endl;
00520     for (int j=0; j<m; j++) {
00521       bool fst = true;
00522       os << "\t[" << j << "]={";
00523       for (int i=0; i<n; i++)
00524         if (bin[i].assigned() && (bin[i].val() == j)) {
00525           if (fst) {
00526             fst = false;
00527           } else {
00528             os << ",";
00529           }
00530           os << i;
00531         }
00532       os << "} #" << load[j] << std::endl;
00533     }
00534     if (!bin.assigned()) {
00535       os << std::endl
00536          << "Unpacked items:" << std::endl;
00537       for (int i=0;i<n; i++)
00538         if (!bin[i].assigned())
00539           os << "\t[" << i << "] = " << bin[i] << std::endl;
00540     }
00541   }
00542 };

00547 int
00548 main(int argc, char* argv[]) {
00549   InstanceOptions opt("BinPacking");
00550   opt.model(BinPacking::MODEL_PACKING);
00551   opt.model(BinPacking::MODEL_NAIVE, "naive",
00552             "use naive model (decomposition)");
00553   opt.model(BinPacking::MODEL_PACKING, "packing",
00554             "use bin packing constraint");
00555   opt.branching(BinPacking::BRANCH_CDBF);
00556   opt.branching(BinPacking::BRANCH_NAIVE, "naive");
00557   opt.branching(BinPacking::BRANCH_CDBF, "cdbf");
00558   opt.instance(name[0]);
00559   opt.solutions(0);
00560   opt.parse(argc,argv);
00561   if (!Spec(opt.instance()).valid()) {
00562     std::cerr << "Error: unkown instance" << std::endl;
00563     return 1;
00564   }
00565   IntMinimizeScript::run<BinPacking,BAB,InstanceOptions>(opt);
00566   return 0;
00567 }
